<!--
    TorpedoMission
    ==============
    Full run, assembled from independently-testable pieces:

      1) TorpedoApproach - board depth, center, close in, arch head-on   (torpedo_approach.xml)
      2) HomeAndFire     - search&rescue_large -> torpedo angle 1        (torpedo_home_fire.xml)
      3) HomeAndFire     - search&rescue_small -> torpedo angle 2        (torpedo_home_fire.xml)
      4) AbsDepth        - finish at 0.75 m depth

    Each HomeAndFire figures out the board configuration itself
    (SelectHoleDepth), goes to the hole's hard-coded depth on odometry, saves
    its start pose and returns to it after firing, so shot 2 starts where
    shot 1 did.

    Choosing the task: this run targets SEARCH & RESCUE. To shoot the SURVEY &
    REPAIR holes instead, swap the two hole_label values to
    "survey&amp;repair_large" / "survey&amp;repair_small".
    (& must be written &amp; inside XML attributes; the node sees "search&rescue_large".)

    NOTE: the torpedo YOLO model is NOT loaded here anymore - the caller must
    run CheckYoloModel (yolov26_torpedo_nano_June17.pt) first. SonarToTorpedoMission
    does this before its sonar-follow stage so torpedoTarget detections are
    already flowing while it rides the pinger.

    Keypoints: the board's 4 corner keypoints only flow on /yolo/tracking,
    which BoardArchStep (inside TorpedoApproach) reads - launch yolo with
    tracking on.

    Test pieces in isolation with:
      mission:=TorpedoApproach   (approach + arch)
      mission:=HomeAndFire       (one shot)
      mission:=ServoTestMission  (just the torpedo servo)
-->

<root BTCPP_format="4" main_tree_to_execute="TorpedoMission">
  <BehaviorTree ID="TorpedoMission">
    <Sequence>


      <Action ID="CheckYoloModel"
              model_filename="torpedo_robosub.pt"
              yolo_node="/yolo/yolo_node"
              models_rel_dir="models"
              ctx="{ctx}"/>


      <!-- 1) Get to board depth, center on the board, close in and arch
              until we face it head-on -->
      <SubTree ID="TorpedoApproach" ctx="{ctx}"/>

      <!-- 2) Large hole, first torpedo -->
      <SubTree ID="HomeAndFire" ctx="{ctx}"
               hole_label="search&amp;rescue_large" torpedo_angle="1"/>

      <!-- 3) Small hole, second torpedo -->
      <SubTree ID="HomeAndFire" ctx="{ctx}"
               hole_label="search&amp;rescue_small" torpedo_angle="2"/>

    </Sequence>
  </BehaviorTree>
</root>
